            h2.page-header Tabs
            p The tabs structure consists of an unordered list of tabs that have hashes corresponding to tab ids. Then when you click on each tab, only the container with the corresponding tab id will become visible.

            h4 Markup

            p
              :markdown
                We use Bootstrap nav-tabs as a base for the tabs component. Simply create a list element and add the `.nav` and `.nav-tabs` classes. For further documentation read the [bootstrap docs](http://getbootstrap.com/components/#nav-tabs).

                You can activate a tab navigation without writing any JavaScript by simply specifying `data-toggle="tab"`  on an element. Adding the nav and nav-tabs classes to the tab ul will apply the tab styling.


            pre
              code.language-markup.
                <ul class="nav nav-tabs" data-toggle="tabs">
                  <li class="active"><a href="#one">Home</a></li>
                  <li><a href="#two">Profile</a></li>
                  <li><a href="#three">Messages</a></li>
                </ul>
                <div class="tab-content">
                  <div id="one" class="tab-pane active"><p>One</p></div>
                  <div id="two" class="tab-pane"><p>Two</p></div>
                  <div id="three" class="tab-pane"><p>Three</p></div>
                </div>

